<h2 id="implementation-reality">🔧 Implementation Reality Check</h2>

Software implementations fail more often from poor planning than poor software. Here's what actually happens during a med spa platform rollout:

**Week 1-2: Data Migration**
Your existing patient records, treatment history, and photos need to move over. Expect 20-40 hours of staff time reviewing migrated data for accuracy, regardless of what the vendor promises about "seamless migration."

**Week 2-3: Workflow Configuration**
Building your treatment catalog, pricing rules, consent forms, and provider schedules. This is where having documented SOPs pays dividends—you can't configure software for workflows you haven't defined.

**Week 3-4: Staff Training**
Plan for role-specific training: front desk needs 4-6 hours, providers need 2-3 hours focused on charting, managers need full platform training plus reporting deep-dives.

**Week 4+: Parallel Running**
We strongly recommend running your old and new system simultaneously for 2-4 weeks. Yes, it's painful. Yes, it catches problems before they become disasters.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Operator Tip:</strong> Schedule your go-live for your slowest week of the year. A January launch during post-holiday slowdown beats an April launch during spring rush every time. Your team needs mental bandwidth to troubleshoot the inevitable issues.
</div>

<h2 id="integration-considerations">🔌 Integration Considerations</h2>

No platform does everything perfectly. Here's what you'll likely still need to integrate:

**Payment processing:** Most platforms have preferred processors, but you may want to negotiate better rates independently. Confirm your platform supports your preferred processor before signing.

**Marketing platforms:** If you're running sophisticated paid acquisition, you'll want pixel tracking and CRM sync. Pabau integrates well with major email platforms; social ad integrations vary.

**Accounting:** QuickBooks and Xero integrations are standard. Test the sync before relying on it—we've seen category mapping issues cause month-end reconciliation nightmares.

**Telehealth:** If you offer virtual consultations, confirm whether the platform's built-in video works for your state's requirements or if you need a standalone HIPAA-compliant solution.

